{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"429e0bde-b4a8-4588-980e-4f00914392a2","content":"Here's the full program:\n\n```csharp\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar person = new Person(\"Alice\", 30);\n\nvar options = new JsonSerializerOptions\n{\n    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,\n    WriteIndented = true\n};\n\nstring json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);\nConsole.WriteLine(json);\n\npublic record Person(string name, int age);\n```\n\n**Output:**\n```json\n{\n  \"Name\": \"Alice\",\n  \"Age\": 30\n}\n```\n\n`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is new in .NET 11 — it joins the existing built-in policies (`CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower`, `SnakeCaseUpper`, `KebabCaseLower`, `KebabCaseUpper`). It converts your lowercase record parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8d7e173a-2d75-4699-8989-196eaa06b3fc","outputTokens":235,"requestId":"EC0B:834FC:BB1A3C:DB9C57:69FE85C2"},"id":"49ecd7b3-23e5-45da-9874-4140cf9b7670","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:54:32.880Z","parentId":"1c8e3771-a4e0-41c0-8bbf-469da648125e"}
